Community members in Elsies River, Cape Town gather to offer their support to the family of Tazne Van Wyk. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Community members and friends are offering their support to the family of Tazne Van Wyk. The eight-year-old's murder sent shock waves through the Elsies River community in Cape Town. READ: Mother demands justice for murdered son Cape Town Mayor Dan Plato is among those who offered the Van Wyk's condolences. Plato says the protests cannot be a one-time thing. "We are fed up with the violence, we have hade enough of the violence and we cannot just continue to sit in our offices," Plato said.